misrepresenting infor�mation in order to attempt�falsely�to put their argument <i>[inaudible]</i>\n","index":"00115","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Now,\nMr. Deputy Speaker, one of the other things�and <i>[inaudible]</i> the member\nfor Flin Flon really failed to do their homework in terms of <i>[inaudible]</i>\nthis bill and how they, as an individual MLA, can support the member for Seine\nRiver and her very thoughtful legislation. ","index":"00116","speaker":""},{"html":"����� The\nmember for Flin Flon�and I did listen intently to their speech, it is important\nthat we listen to each other and hear each other's comments and each other's\nperspectives because it's only then, together� <i>[inaudible]</i> properly <i>[inaudible]</i>\nensure that we represent all Manitobans. But the member for Flin&nbsp; Flon\nasked my colleague about how many times a particular business <i>[inaudible]</i>\nbusiness came in to lobby the member for Seine River. ","index":"00117","speaker":""},{"html":"����� And I\nthought to myself, well, we have the lobbyists registry act, Mr. Deputy\nSpeaker, and I�it behooves the member for Flin Flon that perhaps they should\nhave actually gone down and actually had a look online�which is all available\nonline at the Lobbyists Registry and they would have actually had&nbsp; that\ninformation beforehand and then they could have actually asked a more\nthoughtful question of the member for Seine River in relation to this bill. ","index":"00118","speaker":""},{"html":"����� So\nthis legislation, Mr. Deputy Speaker, this legislation can be summed up in\nsingle word, and it's about choice. And I'm shocked that members opposite and,\nyou know, the Opposition House Leader, who claims that she is a proponent of\nchoice, would deny Manitobans simply whose only situation is they happen to be\na member of a union. And the�my NDP brothers and sisters across the way are\nsaying to those union members, you do not have a choice, you do not have a\nvoice. ","index":"00119","speaker":""},{"html":"����� This\nlegislation in no way impacts the political activities of the unions. If the\nunion leadership wants to take their six-figure salaries and go eat at Rae\n&amp; Jerry's when the restaurants are available after COVID when these\nrestrictions are lessened, Mr. Speaker, that is just fine. ","index":"00120","speaker":""},{"html":"����� This\nis a bill about that opportunity, Mr. Deputy Speaker, saying to individuals, we\nacknowledge and we support�","index":"00121","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> Order. Order. ","index":"00122","speaker":""},{"html":"����� I just\nwant to remind the member from McPhillips if there's a possibility if you can\nput on your mic on. I&nbsp;guess we're having�the headset�I guess we're having\nproblems of actually Hansard hearing you. So if there's a possibility if you\ncan put in your headset in. It's kind of really muffled, the sound. ","index":"00123","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*</b>\n(10:40)","index":"00124","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nMartin:</b> Apologies, Mr. Deputy Speaker. Unfor�tunately, my headset's in the\nback of my car, so by the time I run outside and get it and get back, my time\nwill be up. Is�am I coming across okay for you? ","index":"00125","speaker":"Shannon Martin"},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> Yes, your audio is cutting in and out through the Hansard's\ntranscripts here. So if there's a possibility�is there any way� ","index":"00126","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nMartin:</b> Mr. Speaker�Mr. Deputy Speaker, we'll get through this as we often\ndo. This is one of the&nbsp;challenges of a virtual democracy. But I, like all\nmy colleagues across the way, are blessed to be part of this democracy, and we\nsee the military juntas occurring in other parts of the world so� ","index":"00127","speaker":"Shannon Martin"},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> I just want to ask the member, is he reverting back to the\nSpeaker about the situation with your headset? ",